Conversion Psychology & Writing Guidelines
Core Conversion Principles
Emotional Priority: The entire flow is designed to build emotional trust (Sections 1-7) before presenting the heavy logic (Section 8). The 5-Second Rule: The hero section must instantly communicate "This is for me" (via Eyebrow Copy) and "This is the feeling I want" (via Emotional Headline). Simplicity Over Complexity: The 3-step process (Section 6) is crucial for making the service feel easy and non-threatening.

Writing Voice
Tone: Calm, confident, sophisticated, reassuring, and meticulous.

Language: Use "you" and "your" to speak directly to the owner. Use "we" to show what we do for them.

Style: Elegant, clear, and concise. Avoid "corporate" jargon. Every word should feel considered and premium.

Technical Requirements
Platform/Framework:
Static HTML

Dependencies Needed:
Tailwind CSS via CDN

Google Fonts for Playfair Display and Montserrat

Browser Support:
Modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)

Responsive Breakpoints:
Standard mobile, tablet, and desktop breakpoints.

Critical Mobile Note: The 3-Step Process (Section 6) must stack vertically, and the "Flex Section" (Section 7) must be a single-column list, not a side-by-side chart.

Additional Context
Company/Product Background:
Core Mission: To provide absolute peace of mind to luxury property owners through unparalleled service and transparency.

Key Differentiator: We are a technology-enabled hospitality company, not a traditional management company.

Success Criteria & Conversion Metrics
This page will be successful when:

Conversion Goals:

Primary: Increase in qualified "Book Your Free Consultation" form submissions by 25%.

Behavioral: Average time on page exceeds 90 seconds, indicating visitors are reading the full "sales conversation".

Behavioral: Homepage bounce rate drops below 40%.